'''Imperial Relay Outpost V-798''' was a [[Imperial Navy/Legends|naval]] communications station located on the [[Planet/Legends|planet]] of [[Vaal/Legends|Vaal]] in the [[Outer Rim Territories/Legends|Outer Rim Territories]]. It was the closest outpost to [[Yavin 4/Legends|Yavin 4]] that was maintained by the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Galactic Empire]], and at the time of the [[Battle of Yavin/Legends|Battle of Yavin]] it was staffed by three soldiers, including [[Sergeant/Legends|Sergeant]] [[Reybn]], [[Privitt]] and another [[Unidentified Imperial soldier (Vaal)|unnamed soldier]].

The remoteness of the station engendered a laid-back attitude among the men (for example, they would shoot rocks with blasters while on duty) and fostered a conviction that the Empire had forgotten about them. This, however, would prove to be their downfall. When [[Anakin Skywalker/Legends|Darth Vader]] crash-landed his damaged fighter after the destruction of the first [[DS-1 Orbital Battle Station/Legends|Death Star]] and made his way to the outpost, he led a pack of wild [[Hyenax|animals]], of which he had become the leader by killing his predecessor. Upon discovering the lax discipline of the crew, the [[Sith Lord/Legends|Sith Lord]] boarded the outpost's shuttle without uttering a word. After arriving on [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]] he ordered a ship to retrieve his fighter and bring a new crew to Vaal's outpost.

